# ovh_vps_reinstall (Resource)

Resource used to reinstall a VPS server, especially by adding a new default ssh key

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/resources/vps_reinstall/resource.tf"}}


<!-- schema generated by tfplugindocs -->
## Schema

### Required

- `image_id` (String) Id of the vps.Image fetched in /images list
- `service_name` (String) Service name

### Optional

- `do_not_send_password` (Boolean) If asked, the installation password will NOT be sent (only if sshKey defined)
- `install_rtm` (Boolean) If asked, RTM will be installed on your VPS
- `public_ssh_key` (String) Public SSH key to pre-install on your VPS
- `ssh_key` (String) SSH key name to pre-install on your VPS (name from /me/sshKey)

### Read-Only

- `cluster` (String)
- `date` (String)
- `display_name` (String) Set the name displayed in ManagerV6 for your VPS (max 50 chars)
- `iam` (Attributes) IAM resource metadata (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--iam))
- `id` (Number) The ID of this resource.
- `keymap` (String) Set KVM keyboard layout on VPS Cloud. Reboot your VPS after change
- `lock_status` (Attributes) Lock status of the VPS (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--lock_status))
- `memory_limit` (Number)
- `model` (Attributes) A structure describing characteristics of a VPS model (see [below for nested schema](#nestedatt--model))
- `monitoring_ip_blocks` (List of String) Ip blocks for OVH monitoring servers
- `name` (String)
- `netboot_mode` (String) All values a VPS netboot mode can be in
- `offer_type` (String) All offers a VPS can have
- `progress` (Number)
- `sla_monitoring` (Boolean)
- `state` (String) All states a VPS task can be in
- `type` (String) All type a VPS task can be
- `vcore` (Number)
- `zone` (String)
- `zone_type` (String) Enum values for zone type

